42:40.388 --> 42:44.046
stations. So it's a long process, and that's why

42:44.068 --> 42:47.266
it's taken us so long. It's going to take us several fiscal years to make

42:47.288 --> 42:51.106
up what we lost back then. It is

42:51.128 --> 42:54.740
a concern for us. We are making up

42:55.130 --> 42:58.434
that shortage by increasing

42:58.482 --> 43:01.830
our overtime budget numbers in order to

43:01.980 --> 43:05.446
bring in personnel to make up for those

43:05.468 --> 43:09.126
shortages. But the goal is, the strategic goal is to get back

43:09.148 --> 43:12.986
up to full staffing, because at that point, it would allow me to

43:13.008 --> 43:16.410
make the additional ask for more ambulances and more

43:16.480 --> 43:20.330
inspectors and more capacity to be able to service the increased demand.

