employees, and he's very responsive and he's very committed to what he's doing.

49:46.982 --> 49:50.290
So I'll certainly relay your thanks to him

49:50.740 --> 49:53.936
in regards to the engines and disrepair. Five years

49:53.958 --> 49:57.348
ago, five and a half years ago when

49:57.434 --> 50:00.880
I came here, we had an issue with an aging

50:00.960 --> 50:04.256
fleet. There was no question about that. We had engines

50:04.448 --> 50:07.780
that were essentially catching fire on scene.

50:08.440 --> 50:12.848
That was as a result of the

50:12.874 --> 50:16.264
way they were purchasing these units. They're very expensive. A fire

50:16.302 --> 50:19.380
truck cost us about $600,000 per unit.

50:19.460 --> 50:22.616
A ladder truck is over a million dollars. It's very expensive.

50:22.808 --> 50:26.636
They made a large purchase. They had made a large purchase about

50:26.738 --> 50:31.916
15 years before that, and they

50:31.938 --> 50:35.336
didn't have a comprehensive replacement plan, which meant

50:35.368 --> 50:38.468
that you buy a large purchase of fleet vehicles

50:38.504 --> 50:41.744
at one point, and they're great when they're new, but then they all start

50:41.782 --> 50:44.770
aging at the same time and falling apart at the same time.

50:45.380 --> 50:49.140
I'm happy to report that thanks to the mayor and council and their support,

50:49.290 --> 50:53.120
we've replaced over 50% of the entire fleet

50:53.200 --> 50:56.676
in these last five years. We have

50:56.778 --> 51:00.728
a small percentage that now is outside the

51:00.814 --> 51:04.036
ten year expected lifecycle of these heavy

51:04.068 --> 51:07.896
apparatus. We have begun to focus not

51:07.918 --> 51:11.768
only on the heavy apparatus and ambulances, but we

51:11.774 --> 51:15.708
were also focusing on the light duty vehicles, as we mentioned through some other

51:15.794 --> 51:19.164
creative programs, the lease of these vehicles and

51:19.202 --> 51:22.600
outright purchase of these. So we're making a wholesale

51:22.760 --> 51:26.108
replacement of all apparatus. They're all emergency response

51:26.124 --> 51:29.776
apparatus in my estimation. But in regards to

51:29.798 --> 51:33.740
the engines and the ladder trucks, we have made significant

51:33.820 --> 51:37.404
improvements in the state of this fleet. In addition

51:37.452 --> 51:41.316
to that, the ambulance replacements, we've replaced almost 50% of

51:41.338 --> 51:44.596
those ambulances as well. We are

51:44.618 --> 51:49.056
no longer doing the refurbishing and putting them back into

51:49.178 --> 51:53.240
the system. We're buying turnkey ambulances,

51:53.900 --> 51:57.368
which with all the new safety features that

51:57.454 --> 52:00.808
come with the new apparatus. So that's a better

52:00.974 --> 52:05.384
and safer unit for our firefighters. So in

52:05.422 --> 52:08.924
regards to that, yes, we are well over 50% of

52:09.042 --> 52:12.140
replacement of our entire fleet in terms of technology.

52:12.290 --> 52:15.452
We have made significant investments in that too. We've replaced all our

52:15.506 --> 52:18.476
MDTs and the majority of our apparatus.

52:18.588 --> 52:22.684
We've also switched over our records management system for our inspectors.

52:22.812 --> 52:25.936
Now we're in the in four program. In the past, they were doing

52:25.958 --> 52:29.284
their inspections and documenting on paper.

52:29.482 --> 52:32.640
That's very antiquated, very inefficient. We've made significant

52:32.720 --> 52:36.576
improvements in technology in that respect. Every one of our apparatus,

52:36.608 --> 52:39.604
our heavy apparatus, has a thermal imaging camera. Now,

52:39.802 --> 52:43.572
in the past, that was not the case. So we've provided

52:43.636 --> 52:47.336
that in terms of technology. And so I can point to

52:47.358 --> 52:51.210
a variety of areas where we've made improvements in technology training.

52:51.920 --> 52:55.656
Again, sometimes we can't

52:55.688 --> 52:59.244
get the contributions from the general fund

52:59.362 --> 53:02.556
because of different priorities, but we haven't stopped there.

53:02.738 --> 53:06.352
We've looked for nontraditional funding sources to provide for

53:06.406 --> 53:10.828
training and equipment and health and safety aspects for our firefighters.

53:11.004 --> 53:15.072
In the last five and a half years, we've drawn down almost $11 million

53:15.206 --> 53:19.124
of grant funds that are dedicated for either training or

53:19.162 --> 53:22.896
equipment or improvements for health and safety of our firefighters. So we're

53:22.928 --> 53:26.420
making progress in that. In regards to applicants,

53:28.280 --> 53:32.024
especially for applicants from within the city limits, I completely agree

53:32.062 --> 53:35.032
with you. Matter of fact,

53:35.166 --> 53:39.608
in this last month, I've met with the

53:39.694 --> 53:42.936
superintendent for HISD, the vice superintendent

53:42.968 --> 53:46.396
for HISD, and we're looking at a program to be able

53:46.418 --> 53:49.870
to recruit individuals right out of high school.

53:50.640 --> 53:54.092
The requirement for 24 credit hours of

53:54.146 --> 53:57.436
college hasn't changed. But what

53:57.458 --> 54:00.336
we do know is that there are a lot of students, and according to their

54:00.358 --> 54:03.824
numbers, there are about 6000 students every year that graduate with

54:03.942 --> 54:07.460
an equivalent of 24 credit hours that

54:07.530 --> 54:10.964
come from AP classes or come from

54:11.082 --> 54:14.144
other early college courses

54:14.272 --> 54:17.696
that right now we hadn't been capturing. My goal

54:17.728 --> 54:22.356
is to be able to go directly into these communities that are underrepresented

54:22.468 --> 54:26.472
in our department and recruit directly from high school

54:26.526 --> 54:30.132
onto this organization. When they graduate,

54:30.196 --> 54:33.436
they have choices. Some of them go to college, some of

54:33.438 --> 54:37.224
them go to the military, some go to work. I want to be another choice

54:37.352 --> 54:41.004
for those where we can provide a career for these

54:41.042 --> 54:44.460
individuals and they have the opportunity to serve in their communities.

54:45.040 --> 54:48.224
So we are looking at that, and I agree with you. Our department should be

54:48.262 --> 54:51.264
representative of the communities that we serve. That has

54:51.302 --> 54:55.580
been a focus of mine. If you see our demographics,

54:55.740 --> 54:59.780
we've made huge improvements in recruitment of more minorities

55:00.440 --> 55:04.550
into the fire department. And there

55:04.920 --> 55:08.436
we did some things. We made some changes that just increased the number of

55:08.458 --> 55:11.280
qualified applicants. The standards haven't changed.

55:11.360 --> 55:15.124
Okay. But if we can have a bigger pool of applicants,

55:15.172 --> 55:18.744
then we can be more selective as far as who can come in. We're not

55:18.782 --> 55:22.812
having any trouble filling the classes that we have for

55:22.866 --> 55:26.284
the academy. We have had some challenges, especially during

55:26.322 --> 55:30.808
the Pandemic, where we had to do remote learning in classes via virtually,

55:30.984 --> 55:34.304
because getting a certification for an EMT is

55:34.342 --> 55:37.970
not the virtual approach is not conducive to that.

55:38.420 --> 55:41.856
The curriculum is very challenging. They need

55:42.038 --> 55:45.376
the in class tuition, so our

55:45.398 --> 55:48.636
attrition rate there has been higher than normal. We're hoping

55:48.668 --> 55:53.184
that has changed. Council has approved us getting additional resources

55:53.312 --> 55:57.524
and buildings at the train academy to be able to provide that training.

55:57.722 --> 56:01.556
So we're hoping that that changes for the better in

56:01.578 --> 56:04.936
regard to hurricane season and the assets. When I got here in

56:04.958 --> 56:08.516
2017, we had Harvey. We didn't have any high water vehicles.

56:08.548 --> 56:11.560
Matter of fact, we had one, and that was from District A,

56:11.630 --> 56:14.860
and we got that vehicle the day that Harvey made

56:14.930 --> 56:18.332
landfall. Since then, we've made

56:18.386 --> 56:21.852
tremendous progress. Now we have 15 high water

56:21.906 --> 56:24.190
vehicles that are spread out throughout the city.

56:25.460 --> 56:28.956
We've replaced our boats. Those are all serviceable.

56:29.068 --> 56:32.704
We have an 80 member water strike team that is now trained and

56:32.742 --> 56:36.304
equipped and ready to deploy and augment for

56:36.342 --> 56:38.900
these resources for these incidents.

56:39.400 --> 56:43.504
And we've also made partnerships.

56:43.632 --> 56:46.836
We've used our network with other departments to be

56:46.858 --> 56:50.296
able to meet the training requirements and to

56:50.318 --> 56:53.156
be able to scale up if required.

56:53.348 --> 56:57.112
One example is we've partnered with Public

56:57.166 --> 57:00.376
Works. Do you know how many people fit in the

57:00.398 --> 57:03.630
back of a dump truck? 38. Yes, I do.

57:05.040 --> 57:08.476
Yes, sir. And the reason we know that is because we've used those in the

57:08.498 --> 57:12.252
past, but now we've incorporated them into the Cat

57:12.306 --> 57:16.064
system. So if we expect a

57:16.182 --> 57:19.292
hurricane or some inclement weather, we will deploy

57:19.436 --> 57:23.692
resources from Public Works in other areas into our fire stations,

57:23.756 --> 57:27.460
and they'll have a firefighter assigned to them to be able to

57:27.610 --> 57:31.316
manage and be an additional asset in addition to

57:31.498 --> 57:35.348
what we have. So we have made tremendous strides in

57:35.354 --> 57:38.470
that respect as well. In these short five years.

57:39.260 --> 57:42.728
The resources are spread out throughout the city.

57:42.894 --> 57:48.200
Okay. And that is a tactical decision,

57:49.100 --> 57:51.416
but they're deployable anywhere in the city.

57:51.518 --> 57:53.630
Okay. Shift. Absolutely.

57:56.000 --> 57:59.390
One is that we can't put all the resources in one area because

57:59.760 --> 58:03.580
there may not be enough room. But we do know, and based on

58:03.730 --> 58:07.184
what we anticipate, as far as if there's a certain area that we're more

58:07.222 --> 58:11.056
concerned about, then we will shift resources and pre deploy them to

58:11.158 --> 58:14.624
a little bit closer. But those resources are city

58:14.662 --> 58:18.156
of Houston resources, the fire department's resources. It doesn't mean that they belong

58:18.188 --> 58:21.456
to a certain district. We keep them in certain areas,

58:21.488 --> 58:24.996
but we can deploy them and shift as needed. So my

58:25.018 --> 58:28.564
only concern at this point is hopefully the council sees the

58:28.602 --> 58:32.344
benefit of scaling you up compared to the county scaling up

58:32.382 --> 58:36.036
the sheriff's department so that you can actually stand in the breach

58:36.148 --> 58:39.592
if and when and really not if, when the next

58:39.646 --> 58:43.832
natural disaster hits our city that has to deal with water rescue.

58:43.896 --> 58:47.150
Right. Well, look, again,

58:47.680 --> 58:50.940
we welcome those additional resources,

58:51.760 --> 58:55.520
but we are certainly also reaching out to other

58:55.670 --> 58:59.228
response agencies to have a unified

58:59.324 --> 59:02.928
front and in response to our community's needs.

59:03.094 --> 59:06.948
We work very well with the Houston Police Department. We work very well with

59:07.034 --> 59:10.212
the Harris County Sheriff's Department. We work very well with Public

59:10.266 --> 59:12.820
Works and all other city departments.

59:13.560 --> 59:18.080
We have a good network of personnel

59:18.240 --> 59:20.790
that train together.

59:21.320 --> 59:25.016
We're familiar with each other's capabilities and the resources that we can come

59:25.038 --> 59:28.376
to bring to bear in case we need it, because I think

59:28.398 --> 59:31.896
that's a more efficient way of meeting the expected

59:31.928 --> 59:34.830
risk of this community strategic partnership. Absolutely.

59:35.360 --> 59:39.164
And the key is to have those partnerships in place before the

59:39.202 --> 59:41.630
disaster happens. Thank you very much.

